        "headline": "USN-8062-2: curl vulnerabilities",
        "content": {
          "excerpt_text": "USN-8062-1 fixed vulnerabilities in curl. This update provides the corresponding update for CVE-2025-14017, CVE-2025-15079, and CVE-2025-15224 for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS, Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, Ubuntu 18.04 LTS, and Ubuntu 20.04 LTS. Original advisory details: It was discovered that curl incorrectly handled cookies when redirected from secure to insecure connections. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service, or obtain sensitive information. This issue only affected Ubuntu...",
          "lang": "en"
        },
